1st Project. Write A Data Science Blog Post¶

Kyungjin Cho(2021.02.28)¶

1. Business Understanding¶

Korean Employment platforms 'Job Korea' and 'Albamon' announced on the 6th that the "Satisfactory Level of Salary (46.9%)" ranked first as a result of a survey of 1,288 adult men and women on the "Standards of Job Choice and Maintenance Factors." Other important factors were △ whether they can do what they want (40.8%), △ whether they can do the job they want (39.7%), △ whether they have a growth opportunity for their development (34.6%) △ whether they can move to a better place (22.0%).
Like the results of the survey, there are many factors to consider when choosing a job such as aptitude, ability, vision and money. If we know the required aptitude and ability for that job, it will be very helpful when we make a decision. Therefore, I'd like to figure out these factors that we need to consider before pursuing prgrammer career.

Base on the available data seeing below, I'd like to figure out answer of following questions.

I. What are the most wanted programming language and framework?
II. What are the factors that affect career satisfaction?
III. What are the factors that affect job satisfaction?

2. Data Understanding¶

I analyzed the data after downloading Stackoverflow's 2017 Survey.
After then, I tried to find the characteristics of respondents.

Also, I found that the data involves lots of missing data. I had to clean data to increase its accuracy.
I used 'dropna' function to clean the data. The 'fillna' function was not proper because of two reasons.
Firstly, it was difficult to figure out average value for all categories.
Also, the survey results included lots of resultant response.

I figured out necessary categories for data analysis, and deleted missing data.
Also, I decided to clean the data that includes complicated responses when I analyze it for efficiency. I wanted to analyze two kinds of subjects, and both categories involved complicated data.

4. Data Modeling¶

Regression analysis was used for data analysis although there are diverse modeling techniques. According to Wikipedia, regression analysis is a set of statistical process for estimating the relationships between a dependent variable and one or more independent variables.

I decided to utilize regression analysis for this data becuase of the below reason.

Fist of all, this data had lots of variables. I wanted to figure out relationships between the independent and dependent variables after analyzing related variables with each other. I forecasted that relationships between existing variables has a interpretation after exploring the data by plotting it on a graph. Also, responses were composed of numerical values and texts. Therefore, there was limitation to utilize diverse techniques because of this fixed dataset.

def get_description(column_name, schema=schema):
    '''
    INPUT - schema - pandas dataframe with the schema of the developers survey
            column_name - string - the name of the column you would like to know about
    OUTPUT - 
            desc - string - the description of the column
    '''
    desc = list(schema[schema['Column'] == column_name]['Question'])[0]
    return desc

# Set the possible values and make a graph
possible_vals = ["JavaScript", "Python", "Java", "C#", "SQL", "C++",
                 "TypeScript", "Swift", "PHP", "Go", "Scala", "Smalltalk",
                 "Ruby", "F#", "Other"]

def clean_and_plot(df, title='Language People Want', plot=True):
    '''
    INPUT 
        df - a dataframe holding the WantWorkLanguage column
        title - string the title of your plot
        axis - axis object
        plot - bool providing whether or not you want a plot back
        
    OUTPUT
        study_df - a dataframe with the count of how many individuals
        Displays a plot of pretty things related to the WantWorkLanguage column.
    '''
    language = df['WantWorkLanguage'].value_counts().reset_index()
    language.rename(columns={'index': 'language', 'WantWorkLanguage': 'count'}, inplace=True)
    language_df = t.total_count(language, 'language', 'count', possible_vals)

    language_df.set_index('language', inplace=True)
    if plot:
        (language_df/language_df.sum()).plot(kind='bar', legend=None);
        plt.title(title);
        plt.show()
    props_language_df = language_df/language_df.sum()
    return props_language_df
    
props_df = clean_and_plot(df)

▷ Most popular languages are Java, JavaScript, Python, SQL and C#.

        title - string the title of your plot
        axis - axis object
        plot - bool providing whether or not you want a plot back
        
    OUTPUT
        study_df - a dataframe with the count of how many individuals
        Displays a plot of pretty things related to the WantWorkFramework column.
    '''
    frame = df['WantWorkFramework'].value_counts().reset_index()
    frame.rename(columns={'index': 'framework', 'WantWorkFramework': 'count'}, inplace=True)
    frame_df = t.total_count(frame, 'framework', 'count', possible_vals)

    frame_df.set_index('framework', inplace=True)
    if plot:
        (frame_df/frame_df.sum()).plot(kind='bar', legend=None);
        plt.title(title);
        plt.show()
    props_frame_df = frame_df/frame_df.sum()
    return props_frame_df
    
props_df = clean_and_plot(df)

▷ Most popular frameworks are Node.js, AngularJS, React, NET Core and Xamarin.

5. Data Evaluation¶

Base on the available data seeing above, I figured out answer of following questions.

I. What are the most wanted programming language and framework?
II. What are the factors that affect career satisfaction?
III. What are the factors that affect job satisfaction?

I. What are the most wanted programming language and framework?
We could figure out the languages that respondents have done done extensive development work in over the past year, and which they want to work in over the next year. According to the survey result, most popular languages are Java, JavaScript, Python, SQL and C#. 18% of respondents preferred Java, and 15% of respondents wanted JavaScript. Python was also popular among respondents, and 12% of respondents chose this language.

We could figure out the libraries, frameworks and tools that respondents have done done extensive development work in over the past year, and which they want to work in over the next year. According to the survey result, most popular frameworks are Node.js, AngularJS, React, Net Core and Xamarin. 22% of respondents preferred Node.js, and 18% of respondents wanted AngularJS. React was also popular among respondents, and 17% of respondents chose this framework.

II. What are the factors that affect career satisfaction?
According to the survey result, employees who couldn't be employed although they had looked for job had the lowest career satisfaction. Retired employees had the highest career satisfaction. Full time employees had similar career satisfaction as employees who are independent contractor, freelancer , self-employed. Also, employees who never worked from home had the lowest career satisfaction.

According to the survey result, respondents who are employees of startup had the highest career satisfaction. However, respondents who are employees of state-owned company had the lowest career satisfaction. Employees who used to program as a hobby and contribute to open source projects had the highest career satisfaction. However, employees who don't program as a hobby had the lowest career satisfaction.

III. What are the factors that affect job satisfaction?
According to the survey result, there is a strong connection between job satisfaction and career satisfaction. That is, if there are factors that affect career satisfaction, job satisfaction can be influenced by these factors. Also, salary and stack overflow satisfaction have an effect on job satisfaction. Employees who receive lots of salary and have high stack overflow satisfaction may have high job satisfaction.
